{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3464229,"name":"Rich Jr","username":"rich.varone","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/rich.varone/{size}/167373_2.png","created_at":"2024-12-28T06:12:04.249Z","cooked":"<p>So I’m not sure what the life of the current NI Driver Station software is with the new control system, but I assume its not going anywhere anytime soon so I’d like to find a solution to this issue we’ve been having.</p>
<p>Assuming there are no update’s on NI’s side to resolve this does anyone have any tricks/know how to “better curate” a list of devices to show up here? We’ve been playing with new controllers and really like the SCUF Envision Pro, but it’s 1 downside is that it comes up as AT LEAST 6 different entries on the usb tab, only 1 entry is valid, in this case its <span class="hashtag-raw">#4</span>, the others have either no buttons/axes that come up or only a few (on our development PCs we also have the other issue of our space mice coming up as 3 entries but that’s not an issue for the driver station). So on some PC configs, and when using more then 1, it’s impossible to find the correct one as it’s past index <span class="hashtag-raw">#5</span>.</p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/d/8/d8c6c1069daafaee913d300da48857e80ae950f1.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="uVGXEmAG3uJIbCqm1HbRGyzXPRT" width="497" height="225"></p>
<p>One nice quality of life update to the NI <span class="abbreviation">DS<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Driver Station"></template></span> would be if they find an entry that has 0 axes, buttons, pov, etc to just ignore it.</p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/a/1/a17fd93f9f8770296f0d47c85d424da2aee91ae2.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="n2GMNQRznsXz8NVtbHfP9QLgIPE" width="581" height="291"></p>
<p>Even if we happen to get 2 plugged into a <span class="abbreviation">DS<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Driver Station"></template></span> and get them into slots <span class="hashtag-raw">#1</span> and <span class="hashtag-raw">#2</span>, we wouldn’t want to risk some re-enumeration at a competition that would make them inaccessible.</p>
<p>So does anyone have any advice here, or are we forced to continue on our search for another controller.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2024-12-28T06:12:04.249Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":32,"reads":182,"readers_count":181,"score":196.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":477452,"topic_slug":"driver-station-usb-joystick-question","display_username":"Rich Jr","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":6998,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"FRC 271 | Lead Mentor | Fabworks Discount Code: FRC271"},"post_url":"/t/driver-station-usb-joystick-question/477452/1","custom_user_title":"FRC 271 | Lead Mentor | Fabworks Discount Code: FRC271","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3464285,"name":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","username":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/slab-mr.thomas/{size}/182153_2.png","created_at":"2024-12-28T13:19:47.760Z","cooked":"<p>You can disable USB devices in the Windows Device Manager. I don’t know how easy it will be to identify which ones you want to disable. There might be some properties that might identify the various entries.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2024-12-28T13:19:47.760Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incomin